#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.37:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.37:0.2"
msgid "4. devatāvagga"
msgstr "4. Deities"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Chaḷaṅgadānasutta"
msgstr "37. A Gift With Six Factors"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.336"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.37:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

# Not sure why BB uses perfect here, the tense is the same as the next sentence.
msgctxt "an6.37:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena veḷukaṇḍakī nandamātā upāsikā "
"sāriputtamoggallānappamukhe bhikkhusaṃghe chaḷaṅgasamannāgataṃ dakkhiṇaṃ "
"patiṭṭhāpeti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother, was preparing a teacher’s "
"offering for the mendicant Saṅgha headed by Sāriputta and Moggallāna."

msgctxt "an6.37:1.3"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho bhagavā dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena "
"veḷukaṇḍakiṃ nandamātaraṃ upāsikaṃ sāriputtamoggallānappamukhe bhikkhusaṃghe "
"chaḷaṅgasamannāgataṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhāpentiṃ."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha saw her doing this, with his clairvoyance that is purified and "
"superhuman,"

msgctxt "an6.37:1.4"
msgid "Disvā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and he addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.37:1.5"
msgid ""
"“esā, bhikkhave, veḷukaṇḍakī nandamātā upāsikā sāriputtamoggallānappamukhe "
"bhikkhusaṃghe chaḷaṅgasamannāgataṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhāpeti."
msgstr ""
"“This Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother, is preparing a teacher’s offering for the "
"mendicant Saṅgha headed by Sāriputta and Moggallāna."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.37:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, chaḷaṅgasamannāgatā dakkhiṇā hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a teacher’s offering have six factors?"

msgctxt "an6.37:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, dāyakassa tīṇaṅgāni honti, paṭiggāhakānaṃ tīṇaṅgāni."
msgstr "Three factors apply to the donor and three to the recipients."

msgctxt "an6.37:2.3"
msgid "Katamāni dāyakassa tīṇaṅgāni?"
msgstr "What three factors apply to the donor?"

# The nuance in the terms for positive emotions here is interesting. sumana is a more general sense of well-being, good mood. Pasada comes in the act of doing. While attamana is the result of something. I render the latter more literally, sometimes it just means “pleased”, but it usually refers to an uplifting emotion that results from something positive.
msgctxt "an6.37:2.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako pubbeva dānā sumano hoti, dadaṃ cittaṃ pasādeti, "
"datvā attamano hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a donor is in a good mood before giving, while giving they feel "
"confident, and after giving they’re uplifted."

msgctxt "an6.37:2.5"
msgid "Imāni dāyakassa tīṇaṅgāni."
msgstr "These three factors apply to the donor."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.37:3.1"
msgid "Katamāni paṭiggāhakānaṃ tīṇaṅgāni?"
msgstr "What three factors apply to the recipients?"

msgctxt "an6.37:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, paṭiggāhakā vītarāgā vā honti rāgavinayāya vā paṭipannā, "
"vītadosā vā honti dosavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītamohā vā honti mohavinayāya "
"vā paṭipannā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when the recipients are free of greed, hate, and delusion, or "
"practicing to be free of them."

msgctxt "an6.37:3.3"
msgid "Imāni paṭiggāhakānaṃ tīṇaṅgāni."
msgstr "These three factors apply to the recipients."

msgctxt "an6.37:3.4"
msgid "Iti dāyakassa tīṇaṅgāni, paṭiggāhakānaṃ tīṇaṅgāni."
msgstr "Thus three factors apply to the donor and three to the recipients."

msgctxt "an6.37:3.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, chaḷaṅgasamannāgatā dakkhiṇā hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a teacher’s offering has six factors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.37:4.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ chaḷaṅgasamannāgatāya, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇāya na sukaraṃ puññassa "
"pamāṇaṃ gahetuṃ:"
msgstr "It’s not easy to grasp the merit of such an offering by saying that"

msgctxt "an6.37:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘ettako puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko sukhavipāko "
"saggasaṃvattaniko iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"this is the extent of their overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that "
"nurtures happiness and is conducive to heaven, ripening in happiness and "
"leading to heaven. And it leads to what is likable, desirable, agreeable, to "
"welfare and happiness."

#. VAR: asaṅkhyeyyo → asaṅkheyyo (bj, s1-3, km) | asaṃkheyyo (pts1)
msgctxt "an6.37:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of merit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.337"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.37:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde na sukaraṃ udakassa pamāṇaṃ gahetuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"It’s like trying to grasp how much water is in the ocean. It’s not easy to "
"say"

msgctxt "an6.37:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘ettakāni udakāḷhakānīti vā ettakāni udakāḷhakasatānīti vā ettakāni "
"udakāḷhakasahassānīti vā ettakāni udakāḷhakasatasahassānī’ti vā."
msgstr ""
"how many gallons, how many hundreds, thousands, hundreds of thousands of "
"gallons there are."

msgctxt "an6.37:5.3"
msgid "Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāudakakkhandhotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of water."

msgctxt "an6.37:5.4"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, evaṃ chaḷaṅgasamannāgatāya dakkhiṇāya na sukaraṃ "
"puññassa pamāṇaṃ gahetuṃ:"
msgstr "In the same way, it’s not easy to grasp the merit of such an offering …"

msgctxt "an6.37:5.5"
msgid ""
"‘ettako puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko sukhavipāko "
"saggasaṃvattaniko iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.37:5.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchatī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.37:6.1"
msgid "“Pubbeva dānā sumano,"
msgstr "A good mood before giving,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:6.2"
msgid "dadaṃ cittaṃ pasādaye;"
msgstr "confidence while giving,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:6.3"
msgid "Datvā attamano hoti,"
msgstr "feeling uplifted after giving:"

# I feel the translation misses something if the obvious allusion to Brahmanical sacrifice is lost.
#. <br>
#. VAR: yaññassa → puññassa (mr)
msgctxt "an6.37:6.4"
msgid "esā yaññassa sampadā."
msgstr "this is the perfect sacrifice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: Vītarāgā → vītarāgo (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an6.37:7.1"
msgid "Vītarāgā vītadosā,"
msgstr "Free of greed, free of hate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:7.2"
msgid "vītamohā anāsavā;"
msgstr "free of delusion, undefiled;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:7.3"
msgid "Khettaṃ yaññassa sampannaṃ,"
msgstr "this is the field for the perfect sacrifice,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: brahmacārayo → brahmacārino (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an6.37:7.4"
msgid "saññatā brahmacārayo."
msgstr "the restrained spiritual practitioners."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.37:8.1"
msgid "Sayaṃ ācamayitvāna,"
msgstr "After rinsing,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:8.2"
msgid "datvā sakehi pāṇibhi;"
msgstr "you give with your own hands."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:8.3"
msgid "Attano parato ceso,"
msgstr "This sacrifice is very fruitful"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:8.4"
msgid "yañño hoti mahapphalo."
msgstr "for both yourself and others."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an6.37:9.1"
msgid "Evaṃ yajitvā medhāvī,"
msgstr "When an intelligent, faithful person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:9.2"
msgid "saddho muttena cetasā;"
msgstr "sacrifices like this, with a mind of letting go,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:9.3"
msgid "Abyāpajjaṃ sukhaṃ lokaṃ,"
msgstr "that astute one is reborn"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:9.4"
msgid "paṇḍito upapajjatī”ti."
msgstr "in a happy, pleasing world.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.37:9.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
